  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "Hi everyone.\r\nI am forking Arbitrum mainnet through Alchemy and in my hardhat config I set the chainId accordingly.\r\nHowever when running hardhat test and impersonating someone, technique shown in the docs, the provider associated with that signer is still on chainId 31337, despite the fact that I set chainId 42161.\r\nThis causes bugs when dealing with contracts that check for signatures, as they use the chainId.\r\nIs this expected behavior?\r\nThank you.",
