    "body": "Sure.\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solidity: \"0.8.10\",\r\n  defaultNetwork: \"hardhat\",\r\n  networks: {\r\n    /*hardhat: {\r\n      chainId: 31337,\r\n      // gasPrice: 130000000000,\r\n    },*/\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      forking: {\r\n        url: \"https://arb-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/apikey\",\r\n        chainId: 42161,\r\n        //blockNumber: 35355195,\r\n      },\r\n    },\r\n    goerli: {\r\n      url: GOERLI_RPC_URL,\r\n      accounts: [PRIVATE_KEY],\r\n      chainId: 5,\r\n      blockConfirmations: 6,\r\n    },\r\n    arbitrum: {\r\n      url: \"https://arb-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/apikey\",\r\n      accounts: [PRIVATE_KEY],\r\n      chainId: 42161,\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n};\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nDigging through some old issues, I saw a recommendation to set an environment variable right before running npx hardhat test, and make chainId fetch from that variable inside the config file. Is that still the correct approach?",
